'''Transparency Options''' allows the appearance of buildings and other types of objects to be toggled. The ''Transparency Options'' toolbar can be accessed either by selecting ''Transparency Options'' from the options menu ([[File:en/Manual/Options button.png]]), or using {{en/Keypress|ctrl|X}}. All [[en/Manual/Transparency options#locked-transparency-options|unlocked transparency options]] can be quickly toggled on/off by pressing {{en/Keypress|X}}. 
For each type of object setting the corresponding button in the toolbar or using {{en/Keypress|ctrl}} + ( {{en/Keypress|1}} to {{en/Keypress|9}} ) will allow the player to see through it. The current appearance of a type of object can be ''locked'' against being toggled with {{en/Keypress|X}} by applying {{en/Keypress|ctrl|click}} on its option button. Objects can be set to invisible instead of transparent by clicking on the appropriate button in the second row, or by the hotkeys {{en/Keypress|shift|ctrl}} + ( {{en/Keypress|1}} to {{en/Keypress|9}} ).

===Transparency Options Toolbar===
[[File:en/Manual/TransparencyOptions.png]]<br>
The Transparency Options toolbar has two rows:
*The first row defines what map feature is affected, and if it is locked.
*The second row defines what map feature should be invisible ''or'' transparent when the first row is set.

